                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">You need {geniusThreshold} points out of {totalPoints} total to reach Genius. That's 70% of the maximum score. {pangrams.length > 0 ? `Finding the pangram${pangrams.length > 1 ? 's' : ''} helps a lot since each one is worth at least 14 points (7-letter word = 7 points + 7 bonus).` : ''}</p>
            </details>
            <details class="card-elevated p-5 group">
              <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-800 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">Does today's puzzle have a perfect pangram?
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">{hasPerfectPangram ? `Yes! Today's puzzle has a perfect pangram: <strong>${perfectPangrams.join(', ').toUpperCase()}</strong>. A perfect pangram uses all seven letters exactly once, making it exactly 7 letters long.` : 'No, today\'s puzzle does not have a perfect pangram. A perfect pangram would be a 7-letter word that uses each of the seven available letters exactly once.'}</p>
            </details>
            <details class="card-elevated p-5 group">
              <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-800 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">How does the NYT Spelling Bee scoring work?
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">Four-letter words are worth 1 point each. Words with five or more letters earn points equal to their length. Pangrams (words using all seven letters) get a 7-point bonus on top of their base score. The progress levels are: Beginner (0%), Starting (2%), Solid (5%), Nice (8%), Good (15%), Great (25%), Amazing (40%), Genius (70%), and Queen Bee (100%).</p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="w-full lg:w-72 flex-shrink-0 space-y-4">
        <div class="card-elevated p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 text-sm">Recent Puzzles</h3>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            {recentPuzzles.map(p => {
              const slug = p.date.toLowerCase().replace(/,\s*/g, '-').replace(/\s+/g, '-');
